title: Taça Asiática: Irão vence e garante apuramento com Taremi a titular - TVI Notícias
text: [Internacional](/internacional) Taça Asiática: Irão vence e garante apuramento com Taremi a titular Triunfo por 1-0 ante Hong Kong na segunda jornada Triunfo por 1-0 ante Hong Kong na segunda jornada O Irão venceu Hong Kong por 1-0 esta sexta-feira e garantiu, com uma de três jornadas por disputar, o apuramento para os oitavos de final da Taça Asiática. Com o avançado do FC Porto, Mehdi Taremi, a titular, o Irão fez o único golo do jogo aos 24 minutos. Milad Mohammadi, na esquerda do ataque, fez um passe para Mehdi Ghaedi, que recebeu, entrou na área e rematou rasteiro para fazer a bola entrar junto ao segundo poste, batendo o guarda-redes Yapp Hung Fai. Taremi saiu aos 77 minutos de um jogo que não foi fácil para o Irão garantir a vitória, com a equipa de Hong Kong, treinada pelo norueguês Jorn Andersen, a insistir pelo empate até ao fim dos sete minutos de compensação dados. Com este resultado, o Irão, treinado por Amir Ghalenoei, soma seis pontos no grupo C, para quatro dos Emirados Árabes Unidos, um da Palestina e zero de Hong Kong. Os oitavos de final jogam-se entre 28 e 31 de janeiro e apuram-se para esta fase os dois primeiros classificados de cada um dos seis grupos e os quatro melhores terceiros classificados. Com o apuramento do Irão, o FC Porto já sabe que não vai poder contar com o avançado com quase toda a certeza, no mínimo até final do mês.

author: Airman 1st Class Katie Caroline McKee
title: Sheppard instructor receives Commendation Medal for heroism
text:
Tech. Sgt. Dylan Jarvis, 365th Training Squadron instructor supervisor, received the Air and Space Commendation Medal for heroism on Jan. 9, 2023, here after preventing a suicide last March.
Jarvis became a hero after he noticed a woman clinging to the edge of a bridge, ran across a four-lane highway and saved her life.
“There’s not really a thought process. I immediately started sprinting across the four-lane freeway to get to her,” said Jarvis. “She was already over the railing trying to jump into the main highway.”
“When I got her back over the ledge, we sat down and talked about her life, kids and what was ahead for her future,” said Jarvis. Once I built that rapport, we carefully walked back across the freeway where my wife was speaking with emergency services.”
Jarvis’ selfless actions reflect who he is as a person, but also who he is as an Airman as he supervises and instructs junior enlisted Airmen.
“I told them I want to be the change in the Air Force,” said Jarvis. “I want to make things better in the Air Force rather than just complain because I care about the people.”
Maj. John De Laura, 365th TRS Commander, presented the medal for Jarvis' actions.

author: none@none.com (Recorder Report)
title: Pakistan slams India for banning another Kahmiri political party
text: ISLAMABAD: Pakistan, on Thursday, condemned the decision of Indian occupation authorities to declare Muslim League Jammu Kashmir (Masarrat Alam faction) [MLJK-MA], as an “unlawful association”, for a period of five years and termed this as a blatant violation of foundational principles of the United Nations Charter. In a statement, Foreign Office spokesperson Mumtaz Zahra Baloch said that banning of the political parties and persecution of their leadership manifests a desire to stifle dissent in sheer disregard of democratic norms and international human rights and humanitarian law. “The people of Jammu and Kashmir have consistently rejected India’s harsh tactics aimed at consolidating its occupation. These actions blatantly violate foundational principles of the United Nations Charter, which affirm fundamental rights of the people of Jammu and Kashmir including the right to self-determination,” she said. She said that MLJK-MA was led by a prominent Kashmiri leader, Masarrat Alam Bhatt, who remained imprisoned for a period exceeding 20 years. The MLJK-MA is the fifth Kashmiri party banned under the Unlawful Activities (Prevention) Act (UAPA). She said the Jammu and Kashmir Liberation Front, Jamaat-e-Islami Jammu and Kashmir, Dukhtaraan-e-Millat, and Jammu and Kashmir Democratic Freedom Party had already been outlawed. Their leadership is being relentlessly persecuted through prolonged detention and confiscation of properties. The office of All Parties Hurriyat Conference in Srinagar was also sealed, early this year. “India should immediately lift the curbs on the banned political parties in Indian Illegally Occupied Jammu and Kashmir (IIOJK); release all the political prisoners and dissenters; and implement the UN Security Councils’ resolutions on Jammu and Kashmir,” she added. author: Space Coast Daily
title: Titusville Police Safely Locate Missing Woman With Dementia
text:
Titusville Police Safely Locate Missing Woman With Dementia
By
Space Coast Daily // June 21, 2024
Missing Woman had tracking device/bracelet funded by BCSO Project Life Saver program
BREVARD COUNTY, TITUSVILLE, FLORIDA – A Titusville woman reported missing has been found safe and uninjured on Friday, according to police.
“Titusville Police Department (TPD) Officers responded to a call on Friday, at approximately 2:30 p.m. by a concerned spouse of a 76-year-old woman, who was receiving services from a business at Titus Landing, a premier shopping venue located at the intersection of South Washington Avenue and Harrison Street,” said Amy Matthews of the Titusville Police Department.
At the time he went to pick her up, she was nowhere to be found after her scheduled appointment was completed.
Officers responded immediately to the call for service and proceeded with a door-to-door business search within the shopping venue along with coordination of the Brevard County Sheriff’s Office (BCSO) STAR Helicopter.
The missing woman, a registered recipient of a tracking device/bracelet funded by the BCSO Project Life Saver program, which helps locate wandering patients who suffer from cognitive disabilities such as dementia, was signaling her presence within the Titus Landing vicinity via her tracking bracelet from the transmitter connecting to the STAR helicopter personnel.
After receiving critical location information, Titusville Police were able to locate the woman near the movie theater within an hour of her reported disappearance.
“Responding to a missing community member immediately becomes our highest response priority”, said acting TPD Patrol Lieutenant Mark Jennings.
“This positive outcome can be attributed to the swift action from Titus Landing businesses, BSCO, and our TPD Officers, who invested multiple resources to successfully locate the missing woman”, added Jennings.

author: Sierra Whaley
title: Wish Teresa Gagne a ‘Happy Birthday’ as she celebrates 105 years
text: Wish Teresa Gagne a ‘Happy Birthday’ as she celebrates 105 years WATERVILLE, Maine (WABI) - In the year 1919, a lot of historical moments happened. On April 18, 1919, a special woman was born. Teresa Gagne is celebrating a huge milestone, her 105th birthday. Some lunch plans were in store with her family and then they had a party at her Waterville home. The Brunswick native grew up with nine sisters and three brothers. She walked from home to school every single day, two miles there and two miles back. Her hard work and curiosity led her to different adventures and in 1942 she sealed the deal with someone special. “I married a guy from Waterville, and we stayed in Brunswick for two years and then he couldn’t find any work over there so we moved over here,” said Gagne. They made Waterville their home and raised their three kids. Her husband was in the service, and she had a very demanding job herself, she was a weaver and started that career when she was 18 years old. She retired when she was 60. During her upbringing, finding work as a woman was difficult. “There wasn’t much work for women you know, to pick out if you weren’t educated,” said Gagne. “Yeah, I only went to grammar school.” That didn’t stop her from working hard and making a great career out of it which helped provide for her family. So, what is her secret? She said it’s staying active and staying in good health and of course having some fun here and there. “I love to gamble,” said Gagne laughingly. With all that she’s seen in this world, and all that she’s done, keeping her family and friends close are the key to her smile. Happy Birthday Teresa from WABI TV! Copyright 2024 WABI. author: A TARDE
title: Bolsonaro é alvo de pedido de responsabilização criminal
text: GESTÃO NA PANDEMIA Bolsonaro é alvo de pedido de responsabilização criminal Pedido é de autoria do Conselho Nacional de Direitos Humanos O ex-presidente [Jair Bolsonaro](https://atarde.com.br/politica/bolsonaro-diz-que-sera-candidato-em-2026-pessoal-tem-saudade-de-mim-1292532) (PL) se tornou alvo de um pedido de responsabilização criminal pela gestão da pandemia da Covid-19 durante seu governo, entre 2020 e 2022. A solicitação feita à Procuradoria-Geral da República (PGR) é de autoria do Conselho Nacional de Direitos Humanos (CNDH) e do Conselho Nacional de Saúde (CNS). Leia mais [>> Bolsonaro diz que será candidato em 2026: “Pessoal tem saudade de mim"](https://atarde.com.br/politica/bolsonaro-diz-que-sera-candidato-em-2026-pessoal-tem-saudade-de-mim-1292532)[>> PL Bahia entra em 'ebulição' e Eduardo Bolsonaro expõe deputado baiano](https://atarde.com.br/politica/pl-bahia-entra-em-ebulicao-e-eduardo-bolsonaro-expoe-deputado-baiano-1292800)[>> Flávio Bolsonaro acusa ministro do STF de fortalecer facções](https://atarde.com.br/politica/flavio-bolsonaro-acusa-ministro-do-stf-de-fortalecer-faccoes-1292795) Os dois conselhos afiram que Bolsonaro e os ministros Marcelo Queiroga (Saúde), Eduardo Pazuello (Saúde) e Walter Braga (Defesa) teria "sabotado" as medidas para o enfrentamento da pandemia, com posições contrárias ao que era recomendado pela Organização Mundial da Saúde (OMS). Durante a pandemia, Bolsonaro foi na contramão da maioria dos países e de autoridades locais, apontando que medidas como o isolamento social prejudicariam a economia do país. O então presidente também fez campanha contra a vacinação. “O número exorbitante de casos e óbitos por Covid-19 notificados, sem contar aqueles que não o foram, é notoriamente o resultado da política sanitária adotada pelo governo do ex-Presidente da República Jair Messias Bolsonaro que se posicionou na contramão das orientações da comunidade científica, da OMS, e mesmo da mais singela razoabilidade, participando de forma decisiva, por atos e omissões, da propagação do vírus no território nacional, que resultou na morte de centenas de milhares de brasileiros e brasileiras”, diz trecho do documento.
